            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_03",
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Connect to Multiplication",
      "content": "Think: 6 × ? = 18. Since 6 × 3 = 18, then 18 ÷ 6 = 3. Division and multiplication are related — one undoes the other.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {
        "tool": "array_grid",
        "config": {
          "rows": 3,
          "cols": 6
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_04",
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Bar Model for Division",
      "content": "A bar model shows division visually. For 24 ÷ 4: draw a bar labeled 24. Divide it into 4 equal parts. Each part = 24 ÷ 4 = 6. The bar model shows the whole (24) and the parts (6 each).",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "bar_model",
